messages.message: Does anyone off the top of their head, know of any particularly complicated Cypress tests? My (unofficial, because i missed the official signup deadline) IBHack project is to investigate Playwright (because Cypress is annoying) and it's going way smoother than I ever could have expected and I think I might as well try migrating one of the hardest Cypress tests to really assess pros and cons
Nice!! deployment-api-instructions has some funky stuff in there. edit-deployment is quite long. I bet there's some build ones that are quite finicky too
The reviewer-review-dashboard one goes through running a deployment as a manager abd then logging in as a reviewer and reviewing documents from the run, albeit its still fairly simple just long
